.SH NAME
drm_bridge_hpd_disable \- disable hot plug detection for the bridge
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" drm_bridge_hpd_disable
.BI "(struct drm_bridge *bridge "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "bridge" 12
bridge control structure
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Call \fIdrm_bridge_funcs.hpd_disable\fP if implemented and unregister the hot
plug detection callback previously registered with \fBdrm_bridge_hpd_enable\fP.
Once this function returns the callback will not be called by the bridge
when an output status change occurs.

Hot plug detection is supported only if the DRM_BRIDGE_OP_HPD flag is set in
bridge->ops. This function shall not be called when the flag is not set.
